@article{luhmann1981,
  title = {Communicating with {{Slip Boxes}}},
  author = {Luhmann, Niklas},
  translator = {Kuehn, Manfred},
  year = {1981},
  journal = {\"Offentliche meinung und sozialer Wandel/Public opinion and social change},
  pages = {222--228},
  keywords = {cognición extendida},
  note = {\#\#\#  I 
\par
Luhmann cre\'o su [[zettelkasten de Luhman]] usando la teor\'ia de sistemas como paradigma: 
\par
{$>$}*\guillemotleft For both of us, that is myself and my slip box, it is easy to think of systems theory. In any case, it is being presupposed. In spite of this, we choose a communicative theory starting point. No one will be surprised that we consider ourselves to be systems, but what about communication or even successful communication?\guillemotright * (I, p\'arr. 2) 
\par
Es imposible pensar sin escribir (al menos en un sentido m\'as sofisticado e interconectado *\textemdash anschlu\ss f\"ahig\textemdash * ) (I, p\'arr. 3) 
\par
\#\#\#  II 
\par
A diferencia de algunas interpretaciones en foros sobre el tema, creo que es falso que la secuencia alfanum\'erica y el sistema de ramas obedezcan a una preconcepci\'on tem\'atica (puede ser as\'i pero no es una condici\'on necesaria). M\'as bien obdedecen a una agrupaci\'on contextual (no taxon\'omica-clasificatoria) de intereses de pensamiento o l\'ineas de investigaci\'on 
\par
{$>$}*\guillemotleft The fixed filing place needs no system. It is sufficient that we give every slip a number which is easily seen (in or case on the left of the first line) and that we never change this number and thus the fixed place of the slip. This decision about structure is that reduction of the complexity of possible arrangements, which makes possible the creation of high complexity in the card file and thus makes possible its ability to communicate in the first place.\guillemotright * (II, p\'arr. 2) 
\par
\#\#\# La l\'ogica de estructuras abiertas 
\par
- The possibility of arbitrary internal branching. 
\par
- Possibility of linking (*Verweisungsm\"oglichkeiten*). 
\par
- *\guillemotleft Given this technique, it is less important where we place a new note. If there are several possibilities, we can solve the problem as we wish and just record the connection by a link \textbackslash [or reference\textbackslash ]\guillemotright * (II, p\'arr. 5) 
\par
Una nota es m\'as vaiosa cuando est\'a m\'as densamente vinculada: *\guillemotleft Every note is only an element which receives its quality only from the network of links and back-links within the system.\guillemotright * (II, p\'arr. 8), pero si s\'olo est\'a densamente vinculada a trav\'es de una lista de referencias no elaboradas, su calidad es menor 
\par
\#\#\#  III 
\par
Seg\'un Luhmann, la caja de notas necesita varios de a\~nos para alcanzar una masa cr\'itica (III, p\'arr. 2) 
\par
\#\#\#  IV 
\par
La idea de la importancia de lo accidental en la evoluci\'on que Luhmann usa como argumento para promover un sistema abierto (IV, p\'arr. 1) puede ser comparada a la de los procesos iterativos con ciclos cortos de retroalimentaci\'on (evidentemente ligados a sistemas con m\'as grados de apertura que reaccionan din\'amicamente a la entrop\'ia informacional \textemdash{} es decir, a la incertidumbre\textemdash ) 
\par
{$>$}*\guillemotleft The role of accidents in the theory of science is not disputed, If you employ evolutionary models, accidents assume a most important role.\guillemotright * (IV, p\'arr 1) 
\par
{$>$}*\guillemotleft in society and especially in the realm of scientific research order results only from a combination of disorder and order.\guillemotright * (IV, p\'arr. 2)}
}

